Method.name: Map
Method.Description: ClassMethd Map This method implements a hybrid terminology translation mechanism. During initial deployment all translation will be performed using VETS/CTTDM. As translations occur they will be automatically cached in HealthShare so that subsequent translations can be satisfied directly from HS tables. The cache can be maintained based upon a VA configurable number of days, default = 15

Method.name: SaveTranslationMap
Method.Implementation:
Set $zt="Error"
Set tMap = ##class(HS.Hub.HSWS.WebServices.Containers.TranslationMap).%New() Set tMap.ID=pId Set tMap.FromCodeSystem = pFromSystem Set tMap.ToCodeSystem = pToSystem Set tMap.FromCode = pFromCode Set tMap.ToCode = pToCode Set tMap.ToDescription = pToDesc Set tSC=##class(HS.Util.HubServices).InvokeHubService("HS.Local.VA.Terminology.WebServices","HS.Local.VA.Terminology.WebServicesSoap","AddEditTranslationMap",.tObj,tMap) quit tObj Error Set $ZT="" Do BACK^%ETN Quit $ZE

Method.Implementation: set tSC=1 set oldestDate = $h-pDays &sql(declare dotm cursor for select ID into :tId from HS_Local_VA_Terminology.CTTMap where DateAdded < :oldestDate) &sql(open dotm) &sql(fetch dotm) while (SQLCODE = 0) { BREAK Set tSC = $zobjclassmethod("HS.Registry.TranslationMap","DeleteData",tId) if 'tSC quit set tSC = $zobjclassmethod("HS.Local.VA.Terminology.CTTMap","DeleteData",tId) if 'tSC quit &sql(fetch dotm) } quit tSC
